streams

Interface Predicate<E>


  • public interface Predicate<E>
    Specify an interface for a Predicate type to pass as argument to Stream#select. A Predicate instance for type E represents a boolean test to be performed on instances of E. Typically such an instance is made via an anonymous class.
    Version:
    0.1.1
    Author:
    hugo benichi
    See Also:
    Stream

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean call(E input)
      method that callers of Stream#select implement to filter a Stream and remove unwanted objects.

    • Method Detail

      • call

        boolean call(E input)
        method that callers of Stream#select implement to filter a Stream and remove unwanted objects. Null values should be handled appropriately.
        Parameters:
        input - an object of type E provided by the Stream iterator.
        Returns:
        true if the input object passed the test. False otherwise.
        See Also:
        Stream.select(streams.Predicate<? super E>)
